review_title: Feels like more for Google Cardboard
one_reviews_text: The gaze mechanic feels like this game is more for google cardboard. Sincec I played this on the Rift, I'm rating this game soley based on Rift expereince. Good thing that the environment was mostly the same color, because the the type of movement this game has can cause some nausea/dizzines (even though it is slowly moving). I personally don't like this type of movement since I can get dizzy, I just had to focus on areas where it was all white/grey so it will feel like I"m wasn't moving.  Not sure what happened in chp1, but I can't keep going on to chap 2 & 3 as I did not get hooked.
It's a black & white, 360 experimental art experience. Gaze-based navigation. Unfortunately, I really didn't enjoy it. I was happy when it was over. Maybe you will enjoy it more than I did though.
Takes you on an interesting journey through black and white perspective tricks. Shame it doesn't support any positional head tracking at all though.

Chapter 1 done sofar!

"Look to navigate" works,  My Touch units didn't seem to do much/anything!
